events.description: Julius Caesar crosses the Rubicon, signalling the start of civil war.
events.html: • 49 BC – Julius Caesar crosses the Rubicon, signalling the start of civil war.[1]

events.description: The Western Han dynasty ends when Wang Mang claims that the divine Mandate of Heaven called for the end of the dynasty and the beginning of his own, the Xin dynasty.
events.html: • 9 – The Western Han dynasty ends when Wang Mang claims that the divine Mandate of Heaven called for the end of the dynasty and the beginning of his own, the Xin dynasty.[2]

events.description: Lucius Calpurnius Piso Licinianus is appointed by Galba as deputy Roman Emperor.
events.html: • 69 – Lucius Calpurnius Piso Licinianus is appointed by Galba as deputy Roman Emperor.[3]

events.description: Pope Fabian succeeds Anterus to become the twentieth pope of Rome.
events.html: • 236 – Pope Fabian succeeds Anterus to become the twentieth pope of Rome.[4]

events.description: Robert Guiscard conquers Palermo in Sicily for the Normans.
events.html: • 1072 – Robert Guiscard conquers Palermo in Sicily for the Normans.[5]

events.description: Philip the Good, the Duke of Burgundy, establishes the Order of the Golden Fleece, the most prestigious, exclusive, and expensive order of chivalry in the world.
events.html: • 1430 – Philip the Good, the Duke of Burgundy, establishes the Order of the Golden Fleece, the most prestigious, exclusive, and expensive order of chivalry in the world.[6]

events.description: Stephen III of Moldavia defeats the Ottoman Empire at the Battle of Vaslui.
events.html: • 1475 – Stephen III of Moldavia defeats the Ottoman Empire at the Battle of Vaslui.[7]

events.description: Archbishop William Laud is beheaded for treason at the Tower of London.
events.html: • 1645 – Archbishop William Laud is beheaded for treason at the Tower of London.[8]

events.description: American Revolution: Thomas Paine publishes his pamphlet Common Sense.
events.html: • 1776 – American Revolution: Thomas Paine publishes his pamphlet Common Sense.[9]

events.description: The Siege of Dunlap's Station begins near Cincinnati during the Northwest Indian War.
events.html: • 1791 – The Siege of Dunlap's Station begins near Cincinnati during the Northwest Indian War.[10]

events.description: The first steamboat on the Ohio River or the Mississippi River arrives in New Orleans, 82 days after departing from Pittsburgh.
events.html: • 1812 – The first steamboat on the Ohio River or the Mississippi River arrives in New Orleans, 82 days after departing from Pittsburgh.[11]

events.description: American Civil War: Florida becomes the third state to secede from the Union.
events.html: • 1861 – American Civil War: Florida becomes the third state to secede from the Union.[12]

events.description: The Metropolitan Railway, the world's oldest underground railway, opens between Paddington and Farringdon, marking the beginning of the London Underground.
events.html: • 1863 – The Metropolitan Railway, the world's oldest underground railway, opens between Paddington and Farringdon, marking the beginning of the London Underground.[13]

entities.name: Paddington tube station (Circle and Hammersmith & City lines)

events.description: John D. Rockefeller incorporates Standard Oil.
events.html: • 1870 – John D. Rockefeller incorporates Standard Oil.[14]

events.description: The Plan of Tuxtepec is announced.
events.html: • 1876 – The Plan of Tuxtepec is announced.[15]

events.description: The first great Texas oil gusher is discovered at Spindletop in Beaumont, Texas.
events.html: • 1901 – The first great Texas oil gusher is discovered at Spindletop in Beaumont, Texas.[16]

events.description: New York: Automobile Club of America installs signs on major highways.
events.html: • 1901 – New York: Automobile Club of America installs signs on major highways.[17]

events.description: World War I: Imperial Russia begins the Erzurum Offensive, leading to the defeat of the Ottoman Empire's Third Army.
events.html: • 1916 – World War I: Imperial Russia begins the Erzurum Offensive, leading to the defeat of the Ottoman Empire's Third Army.[18]

events.description: Imperial Trans-Antarctic Expedition: Seven survivors of the Ross Sea party were rescued after being stranded for several months.
events.html: • 1917 – Imperial Trans-Antarctic Expedition: Seven survivors of the Ross Sea party were rescued after being stranded for several months.[19]

events.description: The Treaty of Versailles takes effect, officially ending World War I for all combatant nations except the United States.
events.html: • 1920 – The Treaty of Versailles takes effect, officially ending World War I for all combatant nations except the United States.[20]

events.description: League of Nations Covenant automatically enters into force after the Treaty of Versailles is ratified by Germany.
events.html: • 1920 – League of Nations Covenant automatically enters into force after the Treaty of Versailles is ratified by Germany.[21]

events.description: Fritz Lang's futuristic film Metropolis is released in Germany.
events.html: • 1927 – Fritz Lang's futuristic film Metropolis is released in Germany.[22]

events.description: World War II: The Greek army captures Kleisoura.
events.html: • 1941 – World War II: The Greek army captures Kleisoura.[23]

events.description: The first General Assembly of the United Nations assembles in the Methodist Central Hall, Westminster. Fifty-one nations are represented.
events.html: • 1946 – The first General Assembly of the United Nations assembles in the Methodist Central Hall, Westminster. Fifty-one nations are represented.[24]

events.description: The United States Army Signal Corps successfully conducts Project Diana, bouncing radio waves off the Moon and receiving the reflected signals.
events.html: • 1946 – The United States Army Signal Corps successfully conducts Project Diana, bouncing radio waves off the Moon and receiving the reflected signals.[25]

events.description: BOAC Flight 781, a de Havilland DH.106 Comet 1, explodes and falls into the Tyrrhenian Sea, killing 35 people.
events.html: • 1954 – BOAC Flight 781, a de Havilland DH.106 Comet 1, explodes and falls into the Tyrrhenian Sea, killing 35 people.[26]

events.description: Tashkent Declaration, a peace agreement between India and Pakistan signed that resolved the Indo-Pakistani War of 1965.
events.html: • 1966 – Tashkent Declaration, a peace agreement between India and Pakistan signed that resolved the Indo-Pakistani War of 1965.

events.description: Sheikh Mujibur Rahman returns to the newly independent Bangladesh as president after spending over nine months in prison in Pakistan.
events.html: • 1972 – Sheikh Mujibur Rahman returns to the newly independent Bangladesh as president after spending over nine months in prison in Pakistan.

events.description: The New England Journal of Medicine publishes the letter Addiction Rare in Patients Treated with Narcotics, which is later misused to downplay the general risk of addiction to opioids.
events.html: • 1980 – The New England Journal of Medicine publishes the letter Addiction Rare in Patients Treated with Narcotics, which is later misused to downplay the general risk of addiction to opioids.[27][28]

events.description: Salvadoran Civil War: The FMLN launches its first major offensive, gaining control of most of Morazán and Chalatenango departments
events.html: • 1981 – Salvadoran Civil War: The FMLN launches its first major offensive, gaining control of most of Morazán and Chalatenango departments

events.description: Holy See–United States relations: The United States and Holy See (Vatican City) re-establish full diplomatic relations after almost 117 years, overturning the United States Congress's 1867 ban on public funding for such a diplomatic envoy.
events.html: • 1984 – Holy See–United States relations: The United States and Holy See (Vatican City) re-establish full diplomatic relations after almost 117 years, overturning the United States Congress's 1867 ban on public funding for such a diplomatic envoy.

events.description: Sandinista Daniel Ortega becomes president of Nicaragua and vows to continue the transformation to socialism and alliance with the Soviet Union and Cuba; American policy continues to support the Contras in their revolt against the Nicaraguan government.
events.html: • 1985 – Sandinista Daniel Ortega becomes president of Nicaragua and vows to continue the transformation to socialism and alliance with the Soviet Union and Cuba; American policy continues to support the Contras in their revolt against the Nicaraguan government.

events.description: Time Warner is formed by the merger of Time Inc. and Warner Communications.
events.html: • 1990 – Time Warner is formed by the merger of Time Inc. and Warner Communications.
